main event: Four unidentified objects of various sizes, ranging from 6-7 inches to 13-14 inches in diameter, were sighted over Portland, Oregon on July 14, 1960.
interesting points: The objects were observed traveling in a straight line from north to south.
The objects disappeared instantly, without making any sound or leaving a trail.
Several people witnessed the sighting, but no one could determine what the objects were.
The case was deemed not worthy of a detailed investigation due to the lack of sufficient data for evaluation.
The report notes the presence of heavy low and high altitude traffic in the area at the time, but it was not believed to be associated with the sighting.
sighted object: four unidentified objects of various sizes
